  "body": "\r\n![img_0380](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/34264946/33955649-42c778c4-e062-11e7-984e-aace96d2f661.JPG)\r\n\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a tester trying to edit the Group Chat name.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nThe group chat name modified should be reflected in the chat window of all the members.\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nThe edited Group chat name is not reflected in the members chat window. It shows the original name\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Phone A - Open and sign in Status\r\n- In the Chats window click on '+' to open the Start new chat.\r\n- Click on New group chat and add the member belonging to Phone B\r\n- Click on Next to add the group name and Save.\r\n- A new group chat is created. \r\n- Send message in the group chat window\r\n- Group chat created in the members chat window with the messages in Phone B\r\n- Messages can be exchanged across the members\r\n- Click on the top right hand side to view the Members and Settings\r\n- Click on Settings and note the members.\r\n- Edit the name of the chat in Phone A\r\n- Send messages\r\n- Messages are sent across but the Group Chat name is not updated in the member chat window of Phone B.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\nThe change should be reflected\r\n- [ ] ...\r\n- [ ] ...\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: 0.9.12+\r\nPhone A - Samsung Galaxy Note5 7.0\r\nPhone B - Motorola -Moto E4 7.1.1\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (if on Android please replicate bug whilst running adb logcat)\r\n```\r\n...\r\n```\r\n![img_0380](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/34264946/33955440-91e73526-e061-11e7-9301-3709cbc91134.JPG)\r\n",
